You are helping create a reusable widget component following the UI Design System.

When the user wants to create a new component:

## Pre-Creation Checklist

1. **Check if component exists in common package:**
   - Search `package:common/widgets/` for similar components
   - Available shared components:
     - `package:common/widgets/button/button.dart` - Buttons
     - `package:common/widgets/input/simple_fields.dart` - Text fields, date pickers
     - `package:common/widgets/toast.dart` - Toast notifications
     - `package:common/widgets/linear_indicator.dart` - Progress indicators
     - `package:common/widgets/adaptive_root_scaffold/adaptive_root_scraffold.dart` - Root scaffold

2. **If component doesn't exist, determine scope:**
   - Feature-specific? → Create in `lib/features/<feature>/presentation/widgets/`
   - App-wide in user_app? → Create in `lib/core/widgets/` or similar
   - Shared across apps? → Create in `../common/widgets/`

## Component Template

### Stateless Component (Preferred)

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:common/utils/demensions.dart';

/// A [ComponentName] widget that [brief description].
///
/// Example:
/// ```dart
/// ComponentName(
///   title: 'Hello',
///   onTap: () {},
/// )
/// ```
class ComponentName extends StatelessWidget {
  const ComponentName({
    super.key,
    required this.title,
    this.subtitle,
    this.onTap,
  });

  /// The main title displayed in the component
  final String title;

  /// Optional subtitle text
  final String? subtitle;

  /// Callback when component is tapped
  final VoidCallback? onTap;

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return GestureDetector(
      onTap: onTap,
      child: Container(
        padding: EdgeInsets.all(Demensions.paddingMedium),
        decoration: BoxDecoration(
          color: Theme.of(context).colorScheme.surface,
          borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(Demensions.borderRadiusMedium),
          border: Border.all(
            color: Theme.of(context).colorScheme.outline,
          ),
        ),
        child: Column(
          crossAxisAlignment: CrossAxisAlignment.start,
          children: [
            Text(
              title,
              style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.titleMedium,
            ),
            if (subtitle != null) ..[
              SizedBox(height: Demensions.spacingSmall),
              Text(
                subtitle!,
                style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.bodyMedium?.copyWith(
                  color: Theme.of(context).colorScheme.onSurface.withValues(alpha: 0.7),
                ),
              ),
            ],
          ],
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

### Stateful Component (When State is Needed)

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:common/utils/demensions.dart';

/// A [ComponentName] widget with internal state.
class ComponentName extends StatefulWidget {
  const ComponentName({
    super.key,
    required this.initialValue,
    this.onChanged,
  });

  final String initialValue;
  final ValueChanged<String>? onChanged;

  @override
  State<ComponentName> createState() => _ComponentNameState();
}

class _ComponentNameState extends State<ComponentName> {
  late String _currentValue;

  @override
  void initState() {
    super.initState();
    _currentValue = widget.initialValue;
  }

  void _handleChange(String newValue) {
    setState(() {
      _currentValue = newValue;
    });
    widget.onChanged?.call(newValue);
  }

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Container(
      padding: EdgeInsets.all(Demensions.paddingMedium),
      child: Text(
        _currentValue,
        style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.bodyMedium,
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

### Riverpod Consumer Component

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:flutter_riverpod/flutter_riverpod.dart';
import 'package:common/utils/demensions.dart';

/// A [ComponentName] that consumes Riverpod state.
class ComponentName extends ConsumerWidget {
  const ComponentName({
    super.key,
    required this.itemId,
  });

  final String itemId;

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context, WidgetRef ref) {
    final itemState = ref.watch(itemProvider(itemId));

    return itemState.when(
      data: (item) => _buildContent(context, item),
      loading: () => Center(
        child: CircularProgressIndicator(
          color: Theme.of(context).colorScheme.primary,
        ),
      ),
      error: (error, stack) => Center(
        child: Text(
          'Error: $error',
          style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.bodyMedium?.copyWith(
            color: Theme.of(context).colorScheme.error,
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }

  Widget _buildContent(BuildContext context, Item item) {
    return Container(
      padding: EdgeInsets.all(Demensions.paddingMedium),
      child: Text(
        item.name,
        style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.bodyMedium,
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

## Component Design Principles

### 1. Single Responsibility
- Each component does ONE thing well
- If component does multiple things, break it down

### 2. Composition
- Build complex components from simple ones
- Prefer small, focused widgets

```dart
// ✅ GOOD - Composed from smaller widgets
class ProductCard extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Card(
      child: Column(
        children: [
          _ProductImage(),
          _ProductInfo(),
          _ProductActions(),
        ],
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

### 3. Customization via Properties
- Allow customization through constructor parameters
- Provide sensible defaults
- Use named parameters

```dart
class CustomButton extends StatelessWidget {
  const CustomButton({
    super.key,
    required this.text,
    required this.onPressed,
    this.variant = ButtonVariant.primary,
    this.isLoading = false,
  });

  final String text;
  final VoidCallback? onPressed;
  final ButtonVariant variant;
  final bool isLoading;

  // ...
}
```

### 4. Theme Integration
- NEVER hardcode colors or text styles
- Always use `Theme.of(context)`
- Support light/dark mode automatically

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT
container(
  color: Theme.of(context).colorScheme.surface,
  child: Text(
    'Hello',
    style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.bodyMedium,
  ),
)
```

### 5. Accessibility
- Add semantic labels
- Ensure sufficient contrast
- Support screen readers

```dart
Semantics(
  label: 'Add to cart button',
  button: true,
  enabled: onPressed != null,
  child: IconButton(
    icon: Icon(Icons.add_shopping_cart),
    onPressed: onPressed,
    tooltip: 'Add to cart',
  ),
)
```

### 6. Documentation
- Doc comments for public classes
- Describe parameters
- Provide usage examples

```dart
/// A card component that displays product information.
///
/// The [ProductCard] shows the product image, name, price, and
/// an add to cart button.
///
/// Example:
/// ```dart
/// ProductCard(
///   product: myProduct,
///   onAddToCart: () => print('Added'),
/// )
/// ```
class ProductCard extends StatelessWidget {
  /// Creates a product card.
  ///
  /// The [product] and [onAddToCart] must not be null.
  const ProductCard({
    super.key,
    required this.product,
    required this.onAddToCart,
  });

  /// The product to display.
  final Product product;

  /// Called when the add to cart button is pressed.
  final VoidCallback onAddToCart;

  // ...
}
```

### 7. Performance
- Use `const` constructors
- Avoid expensive operations in build
- Use `ListView.builder` for lists

```dart
// ✅ GOOD - const constructor
class MyWidget extends StatelessWidget {
  const MyWidget({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return const SizedBox(height: 16.0);
  }
}
```

## Component Checklist

Before completing component creation:

- [ ] Checked if similar component exists in `package:common`
- [ ] File named `*.widget.dart`
- [ ] Class uses PascalCase naming
- [ ] Uses `const` constructor
- [ ] All colors from theme
- [ ] All text styles from theme
- [ ] All spacing from `Demensions`
- [ ] Proper documentation with example
- [ ] Parameters documented
- [ ] Nullable parameters have `?`
- [ ] Required parameters marked with `required`
- [ ] Default values where appropriate
- [ ] Accessibility labels added
- [ ] Loading/error states handled (if async)
- [ ] Supports light/dark mode
- [ ] No hardcoded dimensions

## Common Component Patterns

### Card Component
```dart
Card(
  elevation: 2,
  shape: RoundedRectangleBorder(
    borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(Demensions.borderRadiusMedium),
  ),
  child: Padding(
    padding: EdgeInsets.all(Demensions.paddingMedium),
    child: content,
  ),
)
```

### List Item Component
```dart
ListTile(
  leading: Icon(
    Icons.person,
    color: Theme.of(context).colorScheme.primary,
  ),
  title: Text(
    title,
    style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.bodyLarge,
  ),
  subtitle: Text(
    subtitle,
    style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.bodyMedium,
  ),
  trailing: Icon(
    Icons.chevron_right,
    color: Theme.of(context).colorScheme.onSurface,
  ),
  onTap: onTap,
)
```

### Badge Component
```dart
Container(
  padding: EdgeInsets.symmetric(
    horizontal: Demensions.paddingSmall,
    vertical: Demensions.paddingSmall / 2,
  ),
  decoration: BoxDecoration(
    color: Theme.of(context).colorScheme.primaryContainer,
    borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(Demensions.borderRadiusSmall),
  ),
  child: Text(
    label,
    style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.labelSmall?.copyWith(
      color: Theme.of(context).colorScheme.onPrimaryContainer,
